HEADWORD: Bilocation
<hw>Bi`lo*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>bi-</ets> + <ets>location</ets>.]</ety> <def>Double location; the
state or power of being in two places at the same instant; -- a
miraculous power attributed to some of the saints.</def>
<rj><au>Tylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

